[31m-## 5. Build / start expectations (Render)[m
[31m-[m
[31m-- **Root directory**: repository root (single `package.json` — not a monorepo).[m
[31m-- **Service type**: Render **Web Service**.[m
[31m-- **Deploy flow**: connect GitHub repo, set Build Command and Start Command, then Render auto-deploys on push.[m
[31m-- **Build Command**: `npm install` (or leave default if Render detects Node and installs from `package-lock.json`).[m
[31m-- **Start Command**: `npm start` → `node src/server.js` (preferred over custom commands unless the user overrides intentionally).[m
[31m-- **No custom build step** is defined in `package.json` beyond install; no compile step.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-If the user changes `start`, keep it aligned with `main` / actual entry: **`src/server.js`**.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## 6. Runtime expectations[m
[31m-[m
[31m-- The process must **listen on `process.env.PORT`** (wired via `src/config/index.js`). Default local fallback is `3000`.[m
[31m-- **Ephemeral filesystem**: `uploads/` is used for temporary Multer storage; Render disk is not durable across restarts/redeploys. The demo **deletes** the file after handling (`unlinkQuietly` in `src/utils/file.utils.js`). Do not assume persistent user files without external storage.[m
[31m-- **Request size**: uploads capped at **50 MB** (`config.maxFileSize`). Larger uploads will fail with Multer / route behavior as today.[m
[31m-- **Endpoints** (for smoke tests):[m
[31m-  - `GET /` — HTML demo[m
[31m-  - `GET /api/health` — JSON: `{ "message": "RealVision API running" }`[m
[31m-  - `POST /api/predict` — multipart field **`video`**, video MIME types only[m
[31m-[m
